<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAPPING SHALES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I was surprised by Tom Shales' column on MTV's "Real World" ("MTV's 'Real' Mix 
Makes for a San Francisco Treat," TV Times, July 10).He refers to Mohammed as 
"a rapper who calls himself a musician," and implores the young man to "GET A 
JOB." Tough words from a guy who watches TV for a living. 
</P>
<P>
 Doesn't he realize rap music has been a commanding force for over a decade and 
good rappers make the kind of money he can only dream about? Given his 
condescending attitude and limited grasp of modern music, perhaps Shales, not 
Mohammed, should get a job ... in another line of work. 
</P>
<P>
 Mark Davis (Dog), Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
