<P>
 MESSENGER BIRD by Dan McCall (Harcourt Brace: $9.95; 208 pp.). McCall's 
understated novel rings with the honesty of a silver dollar on a barroom 
table.After completing medical school, Jim, the narrator, agrees to serve for 
two years in a neglected hospital on an Apache reservation in New Mexico. 
Despite his skill at repairing the effects of accidents, brawls and binges, he 
remains outside the lives of the people he serves -- until he meets Annie 
Messenger Bird. The gentle, resilient Annie shows Jim the battles her people 
constantly wage against rampant alcoholism and the brutal theft of their 
identity. In exchange for his services, Jim receives the rare gift of 
compassion. 
