<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP MUSIC CHARTS: 'LION' VS. 'LOUNGE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rolling Stones can't be too pleased about being beaten out by the 
soundtrack of a cartoon--"The Lion King"--in their first week on The Times' 
Southern California pop album chart. And what may be more aggravating to the 
rock veterans is that their "Voodoo Lounge" album, which debuted at No. 2, may 
never chase "Lion King" out of its perch at the top. "Lion King" seems ready to 
reign for at least another few weeks--when "Voodoo" is at its sales peak. In 
fact, don't be surprised if another hot soundtrack--third-ranked "Forrest 
Gump"--slips past the Stones' album. TOP 10 ALBUMS 03,04,42,11 Title, Artist 
(National Rank) Last Week 1 The Lion King, soundtrack (1) 1 2 Voodoo Lounge, 
Rolling Stones (2) ... 3 Forrest Gump, soundtrack (7) 11 4 Purple, Stone Temple 
Pilots (4) 2 5 Smash, Offspring (20) 5 6 August and. . .After, Counting Crows 
(5) 6 7 The Sign, Ace of Base (3) 4 8 Regulate. . .G-Funk Era, Warren G. (6) 3 
9 Superunknown, Soundgarden (8) 7 10 Chant, Benedictine Monks (12) 8 TOP 10 
SINGLES 03,04,44,11 Title, Artist (National Rank) Last Week 1 Fantastic Voyage, 
Coolio (1) 1 2 Stay, Lisa Loeb and Nine Stories (4) 4 3 Funkdafied, Da Brat (5) 
3 4 I Swear, All-4-One (2) 2 5 Regulate, Warren G. and Nate Dogg (3) 5 6 Can 
You Feel the Love. . ., Elton John (6) 8 7 Back and Forth, Aaliyah (7) 6 8 Any 
Time, Any Place, Janet Jackson (8) 7 9 Back in the Day, Ahmad (17) 9 10 Don't 
Turn Around, Ace of Base (12) 10 TOP 10 R&B ALBUMS 03,04,41,11 Title, Artist 
(National Rank) Last Week 1 Regulate. . .G-Funk Era, Warren G. (1) 1 2 Age 
Ain't Nothing But. . ., Aaliyah (7) 4 3 Funkdafied, Da Brat (4) 2 4 All-4-One, 
All-4-One (2) 3 5 Toni Braxton, Toni Braxton (9) 6 6 Ill Communication, Beastie 
Boys (8) 5 7 Same as It Ever Was, House of Pain (6) 8 8 Get Up on It, Keith 
Sweat (3) 7 9 Janet, Janet Jackson (15) ... 10 Music Box, Mariah Carey (10) ... 
Source: SoundScan Inc., for week ending July 17 
</P>
