FOUR-STAR FILMS; 'AKIRA KUROSAWA'S DREAMS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kevin Thomas 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kurosawa, widely regarded as the world's greatest living film director, has 
come up with some of the most beautiful images he has ever conceived -- and 
also some of his most ponderous moments as well -- in this 1990 film. However, 
what works in the film's eight episodes, actually inspired by the director's 
own dreams, far outweighs what does not.It is rich in the varied contemplations 
of an octogenarian artist looking back and looking ahead with humor and 
concern. One of the eight dreams features Akira Terao, left, with Martin 
Scorsese as Vincent Van Gogh (Cinemax Wednesday at 8 a.m.). 
