<HEADLINE>
<P>
TALKS TO END NIGERIAN OIL STRIKE STALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuter 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nigerian oil workers walked out of a meeting with government officials Friday, 
abruptly stalling an effort to end a pro-democracy strike which has crippled 
most business activity. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials of the main oil union NUPENG, which has been on strike for three 
weeks, said their representatives quit the talks when authorities failed to 
produce the union's missing general-secretary, Frank Kokori. 
</P>
<P>
 Kokori has not been seen since July 6 when his family said he was picked up by 
security agents. His release is seen as key to ending the strikes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
