<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: WEST LOS ANGELES; NEWSPAPER LAUNCHES FREE WEEKLY EDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN STEINBERG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The publisher of the Los Angeles Independent newspaper chain has begun a new 
weekly serving West Los Angeles communities. 
</P>
<P>
 The broad-sheet Westsider, published by National Media Inc., debuted July 13 
with a circulation of 40,000, distributed free to residences and businesses in 
Brentwood, Westwood, Cheviot Hills, Rancho Park, Beverlywood and parts of Mar 
Vista. 
</P>
<P>
 Other newspapers in the Independent chain include the West Hollywood 
Independent, Wilshire Independent, the bilingual Edicion Bilingue and the Los 
Angeles Independent. The Westsider brings the total weekly circulation of the 
chain's papers to 240,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The Westsider will focus on community news and features, said Stephen 
Laxineta, chairman and chief executive officer of National Media Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Westside has its own flavor. Basically, its quite separate from the rest 
of L.A. in terms of residents' lifestyles. There is more interest in health and 
fitness, and some of (the residents') entertainment selections are different," 
Laxineta said. 
</P>
<P>
 And, he promised, the Westsider will have "no O.J. Simpson news," leaving such 
breaking news to other papers. SUSAN STEINBERG 
</P>
</TEXT>
