<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA CORNER; FESTIVALS, FEASTS & FAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SAN LUIS OBISPO -- Sushi, martial arts, bonsai and crafts are among the 
offerings at the Obon Festival, celebrating Japanese heritage, July 30 at the 
Vets Hall, 801 Grand Ave. Food, music and dance are 2:30-9 p.m. Free. (805) 
781-2777. 
</P>
<P>
 MONTEREY -- Artisans and actors join forces for the Monterey Bay Arts and 
Crafts Faire, July 30-31. In conjunction with the closing weekend of 
Theatrefest '94, the fair is 9 a.m.-6 p.m. in Custom House Plaza, between 
Fisherman's Wharf and the Doubletree Inn. Arts and crafts are showcased at the 
free event, plus theatrical and musical entertainment. (408) 649-0340. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN CLEMENTE -- The Village Arts and Crafts Fair and Farmers Market is held 
July 31 in the 100 and 200 blocks of Avenida del Mar. Works by more than 90 
artisans are featured 10 a.m.-4 p.m., and growers gather with their produce, 9 
a.m.-1 p.m. Free. (714) 361-0735. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN JOSE -- A musical feast awaits at the fifth annual San Jose Jazz Festival, 
Aug. 4-7. Most performances are noon-8 p.m. Aug. 6-7 in Plaza de Cesar Chavez 
Park, downtown. Performers include the Wally Schnalle Sextet, Larry Coryell, 
Super Sax and L.A. Voices and Tania Maria. Free. For information on the other 
concerts and venues, call (408) 975-INFO. 
</P>
<P>
 PASO ROBLES -- Celebrate the attributes of a favorite herb at the third annual 
Basil Festival, 11 a.m.-5:30 p.m., Aug. 6 at Sycamore Farms. Sample gourmet 
foods, including basil ice cream, browse though herb gardens and herb products, 
and enjoy live bluegrass and blues tunes. Wine tastings also offered. $2, 
general; free for kids 12 and under. Proceeds benefit KCBX public radio. (There 
is a nominal charge for some food samples.) (800) 576-5288. 
</P>
<P>
 Call listed phone numbers for directions. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
