<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; VAN SERVICES FOR WHEELCHAIR USERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two new van services are available for wheelchair-bound travelers in the 
United States and the United Kingdom. 
</P>
<P>
 Wheelchair Travel, which is located in Surrey, about 20 miles outside of 
London, rents right-hand drive vans equipped with power lifts, wheel chair 
tie-down equipment and safety harnesses.They also offer hand-controlled cars. 
</P>
<P>
 The company, which will meet travelers at Heathrow or Gatwick airports, also 
rents wheelchairs, scooters, ramps and other devices and has information on 
accessible accommodations and sightseeing. 
</P>
<P>
 Van rental rates start at $600 per week; car rentals at $290 per week. For a 
brochure, contact Wheelchair Travel at Johnston Green, Guildford, Surrey, 
England GU2 6XS; tel. 011-44-483-233640; fax 011-44-483-237772. 
</P>
<P>
 In the U.S., Avis has implemented a customized minivan rental program at 47 
locations in 29 states through a cooperative agreement with Wheelers Accessible 
Van Rentals in Glendale, Ariz. Rates are $89 a day or $495-$560 a week. For 
information, call (800) 331-1212. 
</P>
<P>
 Full-size vans are available for rent at 80 locations in 19 states and Puerto 
Rico through Wheelchair Getaways, a national network that is based in 
Versailles, Ky. Rates range from $75 to $95 per day depending on the length of 
rental. For information, call (800) 642-2042. 
</P>
</TEXT>
