<P>
 Regarding "Hidden Gems on the Italian Riviera" (June 26): The 15-minute walk 
from Riomaggiore to Manorola on the Via dell'Amore, a narrow path cut right 
into the rock cliff, is as glorious as one can imagine. And by the way, your 
map was wrong. According to my journal (and Michelin's Tourist Guide), from the 
south it is Riomaggiore, Manorola and then Corniglia. 
</P>
<P>
 JAMES T. HUMBERD, La Quinta 
