<P>
ENSURING RIGHTS FOR GAYS AT WORK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Regarding your editorial "The Right to Have a Job" (July 7): Thank you for 
taking a stand on this very basic but important issue. 
</P>
<P>
 As an openly gay person, I have known discrimination.I am proud to live in a 
city where there is a law against discrimination based on sexual orientation. I 
am also fortunate to work for an employer, the University of California, who 
prohibits such job discrimination. 
</P>
<P>
 I know many gay and lesbian people whose job performance and morale are higher 
because they are protected from arbitrary job discrimination. I can only 
imagine the increase in the productivity level of hundreds of thousands of 
American workers if the Employment Nondiscrimination Act is passed this summer. 
 
</P>
<P>
 ROBERT GENTRY 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Beach 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Gentry is a Laguna Beach councilman.  
