<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAZZY NEEDS LOVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I am pleased to read that the collie, Jazzy, is doing well after being 
abused by her owner ("Man Pleads Not Guilty in Assault on Dog," June 4).I do 
not believe that giving Jazzy to a breeder is in her best interest.  
</P>
<P>
 I have been to a few breeders, and although the dogs get good physical care, I 
don't think she will get the individual emotional support and love that she 
will need. 
</P>
<P>
 I hope Jazzy will have a family who will give her lots of attention and gentle 
touches. She needs to be a member of a loving family, not an asset in a 
business. 
</P>
<P>
 VICKI COLL 
