<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: OXNARD; MAN IS ARRESTED IN 1989 SLAYING AT PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A former Oxnard man was arrested in Huntington Park on suspicion of killing 
Guillermo Ortega at Community Center Park in Oxnard five years ago, an Oxnard 
police spokesman said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose Villa, 28, was arrested about 11:30 p.m. Friday by Huntington Park police 
after a warrant was issued and signed by Ventura County Superior Court Judge 
Melinda Johnson, the spokesman said.Oxnard homicide investigators said an 
anonymous tipster led police to Villa, who also goes by the alias Jorge Luna. 
The homicide investigation dates back to June 18, 1989, when Ortega was slain 
at Community Center Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa was taken to Oxnard and then booked into the Ventura County Jail on 
suspicion of murder, a jail spokesman said. His bail was set at $250,000. SCOTT 
HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
