<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 MEN ARRESTED IN ROBBERY MAY BE LINKED TO OTHER CASES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNA CEKOLA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A regional police task force arrested three men on suspicion of robbing a 
local liquor store and is investigating their possible connection to other 
recent robberies in the area, police said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 After an investigation, which included a 2 1/2-day stakeout, police arrested 
two brothers and their uncle Friday after the robbery at Neighborhood Liquor at 
9461 Edinger Ave. in Westminster, said Lt. Luis Ochoa of Huntington Beach 
police, which released information on the holdup. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers from Anaheim, Huntington Beach and Irvine recovered $112 and a 
six-pack of beer taken in the robbery, as well as a loaded .44-caliber revolver 
allegedly used by one of the men. 
</P>
<P>
 Antonio Vergara, of Garden Grove, and his nephews Gabriel Vergara, 22, and 
Raphael Vergara, 18, both of Anaheim, were being held Saturday in the 
Huntington Beach City Jail in lieu of $50,000 bail each. 
</P>
<P>
 Ochoa said that the investigation has broadened to include recent robberies in 
Huntington Beach, Costa Mesa, Irvine and Fountain Valley. In each case, 
gun-wielding robbers held up the stores. During the robbery in Irvine, Ochoa 
said, one of the robbers fired four shots at a clerk but missed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA072494-0228 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 063623 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
