<HEADLINE>
<P>
LANCASTER MAN, 36, FATALLY STABBED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies are searching for a motive and a suspect in the stabbing 
death of a 36-year-old Lancaster man who was found in a gutter along a 
residential street. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said a passing motorist spotted John Brown Avila just after 2 a.m. 
Saturday in the 44000 block of 3rd Street East. 
</P>
<P>
 Avila, who had been stabbed several times in the upper body, was pronounced 
dead at 2:56 at the Antelope Valley Medical Center, said Deputy Diane Hecht of 
the Sheriff's Headquarters Bureau. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA072494-0247 </DOCNO>
