<HEADLINE>
<P>
ASEAN MINISTERS SAY GROUP WILL ACCEPT VIETNAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Six member countries said Saturday that they were ready to accept Communist 
Vietnam into ASEAN, the Assn. of Southeast Asian Nations. 
</P>
<P>
 Foreign ministers of Indonesia, Malaysia, Thailand, the Philippines, Singapore 
and Brunei said at their annual meeting that they were ready to admit Vietnam 
but gave no details on how or when it would happen. 
</P>
<P>
 But sources say the target date for Hanoi's membership would likely be 
formalized by the ASEAN leaders' summit next year in Thailand. "There is no 
sticking point involved. The main question is what are the procedures," a 
senior ASEAN diplomat said. 
</P>
<P>
 On Monday, ASEAN will begin a three-day forum on regional security issues. 
</P>
