<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAUGUS SPEEDWAY; WOODSIDE TAKES 4TH MAIN EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RON STAPP, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sean Woodside solidified his position atop the Sportsman points standings with 
his fourth main-event victory in five weeks and two other divisions featured 
new points leaders to highlight Saturday night's racing at Saugus Speedway. 
</P>
<P>
 Woodside entered the night with a 40-point lead over Gary Sigman, who failed 
to finish the 40-lap feature race. 
</P>
<P>
 Ron Daniels of San Bernardino finished second, followed by Sean Monroe of Los 
Angeles and Simi Valley's Steve Nickolai. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Kelley failed to win a race, but still managed to move to the top of the 
Pro Stock points standings. 
</P>
<P>
 The 27-year-old Arleta resident entered the 15-lap figure 8 main event with an 
eight-point advantage over Simi Valley's Scott Dinger after finishing second in 
both the 25-lap oval feature and four-lap trophy dash, and third in an 
eight-lap heat race. 
</P>
<P>
 Dinger began with a one-point lead over Kelley, but finished ninth in the oval 
feature to relinquish the top spot. 
</P>
<P>
 Gerrit Cromsigt held off a late challenge from Kelley to register his third 
consecutive oval feature win and fourth main-event victory in three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
 Results from the figure 8 main event were unavailable by press time. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Mini Stock division, Terry Limberopoulos took the points lead with his 
third consecutive main-event victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
