<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: BRYAN TWINS REACH TENNIS FINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Twins Mike Bryan and Bob Bryan of Camarillo advanced to the doubles final 
Saturday at the U.S. Tennis Assn. Boys' 16 National Clay Court Championships in 
Nashville, Tenn. 
</P>
<P>
 The second-seeded Bryans defeated third-seeded Joseph Gilbert and Kevin Kim of 
Fullerton, 4-6, 6-3, 6-2, and will face fourth-seeded Alex Kim of Potomac, Md. 
and Nick Crowell of Amarillo, Tex., in today's final at Belle Meade Country 
Club. 
</P>
<P>
 In singles semifinals, second-seeded Kim defeated fourth-seeded Mike Bryan, 
4-6, 7-5, 6-3. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Bobby Rodriguez of Sherman Oaks defeated Al Martinez of Hidden Hills, 6-4, 
7-6, in the semifinals of the Los Angeles Open pre-qualifying tournament at the 
Racquet Centre in Studio City. Unseeded Rodriguez will face top-seeded Otis 
Smith of Los Angeles in today's final. 
</P>
<P>
 In doubles semifinals, second-seeded Brett Hansen and Peter Jeschke of 
Montecito defeated Rafael Huerta of Sherman Oaks and Jason DeVera of Villa 
Park, 7-6, 6-3. Soccer  
</P>
<P>
 The Conejo Valley Rockers have advanced to the final of the under-13 boys 
soccer tournament at the Rose Bowl, and will compete today against a team from 
Sydney, Australia. The Rockers are 5-1 in the tournament and have posted five 
shutouts. 
</P>
<P>
 Swimming  
</P>
<P>
 Kristine Quance of Granada Hills, competing for the Trojan Swim Club, and 
Jennifer Parmenter of Santa Clarita each recorded second-place finishes at the 
Janet Evans Invitational at USC. 
</P>
<P>
 Quance, 19, who holds the meet record of 2:30.10, finished the 200-meter 
breaststroke in 2:32.78. Parmenter, 13, swam the 400 individual medley in 
4:55.94. 
</P>
