<P>
KLEIN FIRES OPEN ROUND OF 69 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Emilee Klein of Studio City fired a two-under 69 Saturday in the third round 
of the U.S. Women's Open at the Indianwood Golf & Country Club in Lake Orion, 
Mich. 
</P>
<P>
 Klein, the NCAA Division I individual champion last season at Arizona State, 
is the low amateur in the event and is tied for 13th with four players at 
even-par 213. 
</P>
<P>
 Klein, a Notre Dame High graduate, trails leader Patty Sheehan by seven shots 
entering today's final round. 
</P>
<P>
 Klein is outpacing several pro standouts, including Beth Daniel (214), Dottie 
Mochrie, Meg Mallon and Amy Alcott (215), Juli Inkster (216) and Nancy Lopez 
(217). 
