<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHEAST: HUNTINGTON PARK; MAYOR RECOVERING AFTER COLLAPSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SIMON ROMERO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "I've always been interested in what our paramedics do, so now I know," said a 
relieved Mayor Ric Loya, who is recovering just fine after being hauled out of 
a recent council meeting on a stretcher after he collapsed. 
</P>
<P>
 The 48-year-old mayor was taken to St. Francis Hospital in Lynwood and 
discharged two days later.Loya, who takes heart medication, said his collapse 
was not a heart attack but a "type of spasm."  
</P>
<P>
 He has resumed his mayoral and high school teaching duties. Loya collapsed 
shortly after the opening of the July 5 council meeting, only hours after 
Mexico's overtime loss to Bulgaria in World Cup play.  
</P>
<P>
 With several helicopters overhead and extra police in riot gear, the air was 
tense that afternoon. Loya said that he felt exhausted by the time the meeting 
began. SIMON ROMERO 
</P>
