<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHWEST: CRENSHAW; MEETING TO FOCUS ON REDEVELOPMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Community Advisory Committee, which is working with the city to help 
revitalize the Crenshaw district, will meet Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Local residents, business people and community leaders are encouraged to 
attend. 
</P>
<P>
 The committee will review redevelopment documents and help draft a 5-year plan 
for a potential redevelopment area. 
</P>
<P>
 In May, the committee developed goals and objectives for revitalization and 
recommended the creation of specific areas for redevelopment. 
</P>
<P>
 The study area encompasses retail, commercial and industrial strips on 
Crenshaw Boulevard between Coliseum and McClung drives, and parts of Buckingham 
Road and Santa Rosalia Drive next to the Baldwin Hills Crenshaw Plaza. Parts of 
Degnan Boulevard, Leimert Boulevard and 43rd Street north of Leimert Park are 
also included in the study area. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting starts at 7 p.m. in the Department of Water and Power auditorium, 
5040 Crenshaw Blvd. 
</P>
