<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EAST: PANEL TO REVIEW ADELANTE STUDY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Community Advisory Committee will hear a progress report on the Adelante 
Eastside study and review its recommendations at a Wednesday meeting in El 
Sereno. 
</P>
<P>
 The report, also called the Eastside Redevelopment Feasibility Study, was 
completed two years ago, but officials are following through on the study's 
recommendations that commercial and industrial corridors be developed to 
increase the local tax base. 
</P>
<P>
 An ongoing study of local commercial and industrial areas will determine 
whether government redevelopment funds can be used to revitalize those 
corridors in Boyle Heights and El Sereno.  
</P>
<P>
 Among the Adelante Eastside study's findings was that most residents in a 
10-square-mile area of Boyle Heights and El Sereno leave the area to shop. It 
also found that most of the local housing is among the city's oldest and in 
desperate need of repair. For now, though, officials have dropped the housing 
component of the revitalization efforts and are focusing on the commercial and 
industrial corridors.  
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will begin at 6 p.m. at the El Sereno Senior Citizens Center, 4818 
Klamath Place. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 264-3807. 
</P>
</TEXT>
